ibmappnNodeCpName.name: ibmappnNodeCpName
ibmappnNodeCpName.description: Administratively-assigned network name for this node in the format NETID.CPNAME.

ibmappnNodeNetid.name: ibmappnNodeNetid
ibmappnNodeNetid.description: Administratively-assigned APPN network identification, which can be from one to eight characters. This ID is used with the control point name to create a fully-qualified control point name.

ibmappnNodeBlockNum.name: ibmappnNodeBlockNum
ibmappnNodeBlockNum.description: The block number is the first three digits of the node_id. These 3 hexadecimal digits identify the product and are not configurable.

ibmappnNodeIdNum.name: ibmappnNodeIdNum
ibmappnNodeIdNum.description: The ID number is the last 5 digits of the node_id. These 5 hexadecimal digits are administratively defined and combined with the 3 digit block number form the node_id. This node_id is used to identify the local node and is include in APPN alerts as well as being included in XIDs. A unique value is required for connections to SNA sub-area.

ibmappnNodeType.name: ibmappnNodeType
ibmappnNodeType.description: Type of APPN node, either network, len, or end node.

ibmappnNodeUpTime.name: ibmappnNodeUpTime
ibmappnNodeUpTime.description: Time (in hundredths of a second) since this APPN node was initialized.

ibmappnNodeNegotLs.name: ibmappnNodeNegotLs
ibmappnNodeNegotLs.description: Indicates whether this node supports negotiable link stations.

ibmappnNodeSegReasm.name: ibmappnNodeSegReasm
ibmappnNodeSegReasm.description: Indicates whether this node supports segment reassembly. This is only supported when segment generation is also supported.

ibmappnNodeBindReasm.name: ibmappnNodeBindReasm
ibmappnNodeBindReasm.description: Indicates whether this node supports Bind segment reassembly. This will only be supported when Bind segment generation is also supported.

ibmappnNodeParallelTg.name: ibmappnNodeParallelTg
ibmappnNodeParallelTg.description: Indicates whether this node supports parallel TGs.

ibmappnNodeService.name: ibmappnNodeService
ibmappnNodeService.description: Indicates whether this node allows call-in from nodes not defined locally.

ibmappnNodeAdaptiveBindPacing.name: ibmappnNodeAdaptiveBindPacing
ibmappnNodeAdaptiveBindPacing.description: Indicates whether this node supports adaptive bind pacing.

ibmappnNodeNnRcvRegChar.name: ibmappnNodeNnRcvRegChar
ibmappnNodeNnRcvRegChar.description: Indicates whether this node supports receiving registered characteristics.

ibmappnNodeNnGateway.name: ibmappnNodeNnGateway
ibmappnNodeNnGateway.description: Indicates whether this is a gateway node.

ibmappnNodeNnCentralDirectory.name: ibmappnNodeNnCentralDirectory
ibmappnNodeNnCentralDirectory.description: Indicates whether this node supports central directory cache.

ibmappnNodeNnTreeCache.name: ibmappnNodeNnTreeCache
ibmappnNodeNnTreeCache.description: Indicates whether this node supports route tree cache.

ibmappnNodeNnTreeUpdate.name: ibmappnNodeNnTreeUpdate
ibmappnNodeNnTreeUpdate.description: Indicates whether this node supports incremental_tree_update, which is only supported when tree caching is supported.

ibmappnNodeNnRouteAddResist.name: ibmappnNodeNnRouteAddResist
ibmappnNodeNnRouteAddResist.description: Route addition resistance is a value that indicates the relative desirability of using this node for intermediate session traffic. The value, which can be any integer 0-255, is used in route computation. The lower the value, the more desirable the node is for intermediate routing.

ibmappnNodeNnIsr.name: ibmappnNodeNnIsr
ibmappnNodeNnIsr.description: Indicates whether the node supports intermediate session routing.

ibmappnNodeNnFrsn.name: ibmappnNodeNnFrsn
ibmappnNodeNnFrsn.description: Flow reduction sequence numbers (FRSNs) are associated with Topology Database Updates (TDUs) and are unique only within each APPN network node. A TDU can be associated with multiple APPN resources. This object is the last FRSN sent in a topology update to adjacent network nodes.

ibmappnNodeEnSegGen.name: ibmappnNodeEnSegGen
ibmappnNodeEnSegGen.description: Indicates whether this end node supports segment generation.

ibmappnNodeEnModeCosMap.name: ibmappnNodeEnModeCosMap
ibmappnNodeEnModeCosMap.description: Indicates whether this end node supports mode name to COS name mapping.

ibmappnNodeEnLocateCdinit.name: ibmappnNodeEnLocateCdinit
ibmappnNodeEnLocateCdinit.description: Indicates whether this end node supports Locate Cdinit.

ibmappnNodeEnSendRegNames.name: ibmappnNodeEnSendRegNames
ibmappnNodeEnSendRegNames.description: Indicates whether the node will register its LUs with the adjacent serving network node: NO - do not register names YES - register names

ibmappnNodeEnSendRegChar.name: ibmappnNodeEnSendRegChar
ibmappnNodeEnSendRegChar.description: Indicates whether this node supports send register characteristics, which is only supported when send registered names is also supported.

ibmappnNodePortTable.name: ibmappnNodePortTable
ibmappnNodePortTable.description: The Port table describes the configuration and current status of the ports used by APPN. The type of DLC is included in this table as a pointer to the DLC port specific tables.

ibmappnNodePortEntry.name: ibmappnNodePortEntry
ibmappnNodePortEntry.description: The Port Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodePortName.name: ibmappnNodePortName
ibmappnNodePortName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this APPN port. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodePortState.name: ibmappnNodePortState
ibmappnNodePortState.description: Indicates the current state of this port.

ibmappnNodePortDlcType.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcType
ibmappnNodePortDlcType.description: The type of DLC interface, distinguished according to the protocol immediately 'below' this layer.

ibmappnNodePortPortType.name: ibmappnNodePortPortType
ibmappnNodePortPortType.description: Identifies the type of line used by this port.

ibmappnNodePortSIMRIM.name: ibmappnNodePortSIMRIM
ibmappnNodePortSIMRIM.description: Indicates whether Set Initialization Mode (SIM) and Receive Initialization Mode (RIM) are supported.

ibmappnNodePortLsRole.name: ibmappnNodePortLsRole
ibmappnNodePortLsRole.description: Initial role for LSs activated through this port, where 'abm' indicates asynchronous balance mode.

ibmappnNodePortMaxRcvBtuSize.name: ibmappnNodePortMaxRcvBtuSize
ibmappnNodePortMaxRcvBtuSize.description: Maximum Basic Transmission Size (BTU) that a link station on this port can receive.

ibmappnNodePortMaxIframeWindow.name: ibmappnNodePortMaxIframeWindow
ibmappnNodePortMaxIframeWindow.description: Maximum number of I-frames that can be received by the XID sender before an acknowledgement is received.

ibmappnNodePortDefLsGoodXids.name: ibmappnNodePortDefLsGoodXids
ibmappnNodePortDefLsGoodXids.description: The total number of successfull XIDs that have occurred on all defined link stations on this port since the last time this port was started.

ibmappnNodePortDefLsBadXids.name: ibmappnNodePortDefLsBadXids
ibmappnNodePortDefLsBadXids.description: The total number of unsuccessfull XIDs that have occurred on all defined link stations on this port since the last time this port was started.

ibmappnNodePortDynLsGoodXids.name: ibmappnNodePortDynLsGoodXids
ibmappnNodePortDynLsGoodXids.description: The total number of successfull XIDs that have occurred on all dynamic link stations on this port since the last time this port was started.

ibmappnNodePortDynLsBadXids.name: ibmappnNodePortDynLsBadXids
ibmappnNodePortDynLsBadXids.description: The total number of unsuccessfull XIDs that have occurred on all dynamic link stations on this port since the last time this port was started.

ibmappnNodePortSpecific.name: ibmappnNodePortSpecific
ibmappnNodePortSpecific.description: Identifies the port specific OBJECT IDENTIFIER that can provide additional information.

ibmappnNodePortIpEntry.name: ibmappnNodePortIpEntry
ibmappnNodePortIpEntry.description: The IP Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodePortIpName.name: ibmappnNodePortIpName
ibmappnNodePortIpName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this APPN port. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodePortDlsEntry.name: ibmappnNodePortDlsEntry
ibmappnNodePortDlsEntry.description: The DLS Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodePortDlsName.name: ibmappnNodePortDlsName
ibmappnNodePortDlsName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this APPN DLS port. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodePortTrEntry.name: ibmappnNodePortTrEntry
ibmappnNodePortTrEntry.description: The TR Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodePortTrName.name: ibmappnNodePortTrName
ibmappnNodePortTrName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this APPN port. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodePortDlcTraceTable.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTraceTable
ibmappnNodePortDlcTraceTable.description: Port table generic DLC trace table.

ibmappnNodePortDlcTraceEntry.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTraceEntry
ibmappnNodePortDlcTraceEntry.description: The Port name and a dynamic integer are the index to this table.

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracPortName.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracPortName
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracPortName.description: The Port name associated with this this trace table entry.

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracIndex.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracIndex
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracIndex.description: This index value is updated every time a new trace entry is created which provides a means to retrieve only the updated entries and also provides a simple method of correlating the entries. The table will wrap when the table is full, which will result in previous entries being written over. The mangement station can over come this by retrieving the table using this index to retrieve only the new table entries.

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracDlcType.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracDlcType
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracDlcType.description: The type of DLC interface, distinguished according to the protocol immediately 'below' this layer.

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracLocalAddr.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracLocalAddr
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracLocalAddr.description: Local address in format described below: other = free form DisplayString ip = ld. ld. ld. ld / 2d tr = lx: lx: lx: lx: lx: lx . lx dlsw = lx: lx: lx: lx: lx: lx . lx ethernet = lx: lx: lx: lx: lx: lx . lx

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracRemoteAddr.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracRemoteAddr
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracRemoteAddr.description: Remote Address in the format described below: other = free form DisplayString ip = ld. ld. ld. ld / 2d tr = lx: lx: lx: lx: lx: lx . lx dlsw = lx: lx: lx: lx: lx: lx . lx ethernet = lx: lx: lx: lx: lx: lx . lx

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracMsgType.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracMsgType
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracMsgType.description: Indicates the type of trace record entry

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracCmdType.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracCmdType
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracCmdType.description: Indicates the command type of the trace entry.

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracUseWan.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracUseWan
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracUseWan.description: Indicates the type of connection of the trace entry. For example, token ring and ethernet ports will have useLan as connection. For the dls port, it could be either useWan if connection is across Wan via dls sessions, or useLan if connection is to a local attached LAN.

ibmappnNodeLsTable.name: ibmappnNodeLsTable
ibmappnNodeLsTable.description: This table contains detail information about the link station configuration and current status.

ibmappnNodeLsEntry.name: ibmappnNodeLsEntry
ibmappnNodeLsEntry.description: This table is indexed by the link station name.

ibmappnNodeLsName.name: ibmappnNodeLsName
ibmappnNodeLsName.description: Administratively-assigned name for the link station. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodeLsPortName.name: ibmappnNodeLsPortName
ibmappnNodeLsPortName.description: Administratively-assigned name for the port. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodeLsDlcType.name: ibmappnNodeLsDlcType
ibmappnNodeLsDlcType.description: The type of DLC interface, distinguished according to the protocol immediately 'below' this layer.

ibmappnNodeLsDynamic.name: ibmappnNodeLsDynamic
ibmappnNodeLsDynamic.description: Identifies whether this resource is a dynamic link station. Dynamic link stations are created when adjacent nodes that have not been locally defined establish a connection with this node.

ibmappnNodeLsCpName.name: ibmappnNodeLsCpName
ibmappnNodeLsCpName.description: Fully-qualified name of the adjacent node for this link station. The name can be from three to seventeen characters. Format is netid.cpname.

ibmappnNodeLsTgNum.name: ibmappnNodeLsTgNum
ibmappnNodeLsTgNum.description: Number associated with the TG to this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsLimResource.name: ibmappnNodeLsLimResource
ibmappnNodeLsLimResource.description: Indicates whether the link station is a limited resource. If it is, the TG is deactivated when there are no sessions.

ibmappnNodeLsMigration.name: ibmappnNodeLsMigration
ibmappnNodeLsMigration.description: Indicates whether this link station will be used for connections to down-level or migration partners.

ibmappnNodeLsBlockNum.name: ibmappnNodeLsBlockNum
ibmappnNodeLsBlockNum.description: The block number is the first three digits of the node_id. These 3 hexideimal digits identify the product and are not configurable.

ibmappnNodeLsIdNum.name: ibmappnNodeLsIdNum
ibmappnNodeLsIdNum.description: The ID number is the last 5 digits of the node_id. These 5 hexadecimal digits are administratively defined and combined with the 3 digit block number form the node_id. This node_id is used to identify the local node and is include in APPN alerts as well as being included in XIDs. A unique value is required for connections to SNA sub-area.

ibmappnNodeLsCpCpSession.name: ibmappnNodeLsCpCpSession
ibmappnNodeLsCpCpSession.description: Indicates whether CP-CP sessions are supported by this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsTargetPacingCount.name: ibmappnNodeLsTargetPacingCount
ibmappnNodeLsTargetPacingCount.description: Numeric value between 0 and 32767 inclusive indicating the desired pacing window size for BINDs on this TG. The number is significant only when fixed bind pacing is being performed.

ibmappnNodeLsMaxSendBtuSize.name: ibmappnNodeLsMaxSendBtuSize
ibmappnNodeLsMaxSendBtuSize.description: Numeric value between 0 and 32767 inclusive indicating the desired number of bytes in a Basic Transmission Unit (BTU) that can be sent on this TG. This is an administratively assigned value.

ibmappnNodeLsEffCap.name: ibmappnNodeLsEffCap
ibmappnNodeLsEffCap.description: The effective capacity is an integer value that indicates the kilo bits per second. It is derived from the link bandwidth and maximum load factor with the range of 0 thru 603,979,776. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsConnCost.name: ibmappnNodeLsConnCost
ibmappnNodeLsConnCost.description: Cost per connect time: a value representing the relative cost per unit of time to use the TG. Range is from 0, which means no cost, to 255, which indicates maximum cost. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsByteCost.name: ibmappnNodeLsByteCost
ibmappnNodeLsByteCost.description: Relative cost of transmitting a byte over this link. Range is from 0 (lowest cost) to 255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsSecurity.name: ibmappnNodeLsSecurity
ibmappnNodeLsSecurity.description: The security is represented as an integer with a range of 1 thru 255 with the most common values enumerated as defined above. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsDelay.name: ibmappnNodeLsDelay
ibmappnNodeLsDelay.description: Relative amount of time that it takes for a signal to travel the length of the logical link. This time is represented in micro seconds, with some of the more common values enumerated. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsUsr1.name: ibmappnNodeLsUsr1
ibmappnNodeLsUsr1.description: First user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsUsr2.name: ibmappnNodeLsUsr2
ibmappnNodeLsUsr2.description: Second user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsUsr3.name: ibmappnNodeLsUsr3
ibmappnNodeLsUsr3.description: Third user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsEchoRsps.name: ibmappnNodeLsEchoRsps
ibmappnNodeLsEchoRsps.description: Number of responses returned from adjacent link station. A response should be returned for each test frame sent by this node. Test frames are sent to adjacent nodes periodically to verify connectivity and to measure that actual round trip time, that is the time the test frame is sent until the response is received.

ibmappnNodeLsCurrentDelay.name: ibmappnNodeLsCurrentDelay
ibmappnNodeLsCurrentDelay.description: The time that it took for the last test signal to be sent and returned from this link station to the adjacent links station. This time is represented in milliseconds.

ibmappnNodeLsMaxDelay.name: ibmappnNodeLsMaxDelay
ibmappnNodeLsMaxDelay.description: The longest time it took for a test signal to be sent and returned from this link station to the adjacent links station. This time is represented in milliseconds .

ibmappnNodeLsMinDelay.name: ibmappnNodeLsMinDelay
ibmappnNodeLsMinDelay.description: The shortest time it took for a test signal to be sent and returned from this link station to the adjacent links station. This time is represented in milliseconds.

ibmappnNodeLsMaxDelayTime.name: ibmappnNodeLsMaxDelayTime
ibmappnNodeLsMaxDelayTime.description: The time (since system up in hundredth of seconds) when the longest delay occurred. This time can be used to identify when this high water mark occurred in relation to the last initialization of the APPN node.

ibmappnNodeLsGoodXids.name: ibmappnNodeLsGoodXids
ibmappnNodeLsGoodXids.description: The total number of successful XIDs that have occurred on this link station since the time it was started.

ibmappnNodeLsBadXids.name: ibmappnNodeLsBadXids
ibmappnNodeLsBadXids.description: The total number of unsuccessful XIDs that have occurred on this link station since the time it was started.

ibmappnNodeLsSpecific.name: ibmappnNodeLsSpecific
ibmappnNodeLsSpecific.description: Identifies the DLC specific OBJECT IDENTIFIER that can provide additional information.

ibmappnNodeLsStartTime.name: ibmappnNodeLsStartTime
ibmappnNodeLsStartTime.description: The time (in hundredth of seconds) this link station has been active the last time since the time APPN was initialized.

ibmappnNodeLsActiveTime.name: ibmappnNodeLsActiveTime
ibmappnNodeLsActiveTime.description: The time (in hundredth of seconds) this link station has been in the active state. A zero value indicates the link station has never been active.

ibmappnNodeLsCurrentStateTime.name: ibmappnNodeLsCurrentStateTime
ibmappnNodeLsCurrentStateTime.description: The time (in hundredth of seconds) the link station is in the current state.

ibmappnNodeLsIpEntry.name: ibmappnNodeLsIpEntry
ibmappnNodeLsIpEntry.description: The IP Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodeLsIpName.name: ibmappnNodeLsIpName
ibmappnNodeLsIpName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this link station. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodeLsLocalIpPortNum.name: ibmappnNodeLsLocalIpPortNum
ibmappnNodeLsLocalIpPortNum.description: Local TCP/IP port number. The default listening port will be administratively assigned and will dynamically change if this node initiates a session with adjacent node.

ibmappnNodeLsDlsEntry.name: ibmappnNodeLsDlsEntry
ibmappnNodeLsDlsEntry.description: The DLS Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodeLsDlsName.name: ibmappnNodeLsDlsName
ibmappnNodeLsDlsName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this link station. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodeLsTrEntry.name: ibmappnNodeLsTrEntry
ibmappnNodeLsTrEntry.description: The TR Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodeLsTrName.name: ibmappnNodeLsTrName
ibmappnNodeLsTrName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this link station. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusTable.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusTable
ibmappnNodeLsStatusTable.description: This table contains information related to exceptional and potential exceptional conditions that occur during the activation, XID exchange, and termination of the connection.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusEntry.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusEntry
ibmappnNodeLsStatusEntry.description: This table is indexed by the LsStatusIndex, which is an integer that is continuously updated until it eventually wraps. This provides the management station the ability to retrieve only the updates to the table by using the standard GET NEXT.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusIndex.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusIndex
ibmappnNodeLsStatusIndex.description: This index is continuous index this table.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusTime.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusTime
ibmappnNodeLsStatusTime.description: Time (in hundreds of a second) since this node was last initialized.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusLsName.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusLsName
ibmappnNodeLsStatusLsName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusCpName.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusCpName
ibmappnNodeLsStatusCpName.description: Administratively-assigned fully-qualified name of the adjacent node partner. This will be provided when the adjacent node has been defined at this node or when the XID sequence has proceeded far enough to to identify the adjacent node. A blank CP name will indicate the name is unknown.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusTgNum.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusTgNum
ibmappnNodeLsStatusTgNum.description: Number associated with the TG to this link station with a range from 0 to 256. A value of 256 indicates the tg number has not been negotiated and is unknown at this time.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusGeneralSense.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusGeneralSense
ibmappnNodeLsStatusGeneralSense.description: The error sense code associated with the start sequence of activation of a link up to the beginning of the XID sequence.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusNofRetry.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusNofRetry
ibmappnNodeLsStatusNofRetry.description: Indicates whether Node Operator Facility will retry the start request to activate the link.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusEndSense.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusEndSense
ibmappnNodeLsStatusEndSense.description: The sense code associated with the termination of the link connection to adjacent node. This includes all sense information included in the disconnect recieved from the lower layer DLCs and also sense information indicating the link termination originated by upper layer APPN components.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidLocalSense.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidLocalSense
ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidLocalSense.description: The error sense code associated with the rejection of the XID.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidRemoteSense.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidRemoteSense
ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidRemoteSense.description: The error sense code adjacent node returned to this node indicating the reason the XID was rejected.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidByteInError.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidByteInError
ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidByteInError.description: This identifies the actual byte in the XID that caused the error. The value of zero (0) indicates that the variable has no meaning.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidBitInError.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidBitInError
ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidBitInError.description: This identifies the actual bit within the error byte of the XID. This only has meaning when the byte in error is greater than zero.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusDlcType.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusDlcType
ibmappnNodeLsStatusDlcType.description: This identifies DLC type that was being used when error occurred. This also is used to the format of the local and remote address provided. other = free form DisplayString ip = ld. ld. ld. ld / 2d tr = lx: lx: lx: lx: lx: lx . lx dlsw = lx: lx: lx: lx: lx: lx . lx ethernet = lx: lx: lx: lx: lx: lx . lx

ibmappnNodeLsStatusLocalAddr.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusLocalAddr
ibmappnNodeLsStatusLocalAddr.description: This contains a displayable string that identifies the DLC type and appropriate address. See DlcType above for details of the format.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusRemoteAddr.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusRemoteAddr
ibmappnNodeLsStatusRemoteAddr.description: This contains a displayable string that identifies the DLC type and appropriate address. See DlcType above for details of the format.

ibmappnSnmpInPkts.name: ibmappnSnmpInPkts
ibmappnSnmpInPkts.description: Total number of messages delivered to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInGetRequests.name: ibmappnSnmpInGetRequests
ibmappnSnmpInGetRequests.description: Total number of GET requests delivered to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInGetNexts.name: ibmappnSnmpInGetNexts
ibmappnSnmpInGetNexts.description: Total number of GETNEXT requests delivered to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInSetRequests.name: ibmappnSnmpInSetRequests
ibmappnSnmpInSetRequests.description: Total number of SET requests delivered to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInTotalVars.name: ibmappnSnmpInTotalVars
ibmappnSnmpInTotalVars.description: Total number of VARIABLES included in both GET and GETNEXT requests to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInGetVars.name: ibmappnSnmpInGetVars
ibmappnSnmpInGetVars.description: Total number of VARIBLES included in all GET requests to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInGetNextVars.name: ibmappnSnmpInGetNextVars
ibmappnSnmpInGetNextVars.description: Total number of VARIABLES included in all GETNEXT requests to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInSetVars.name: ibmappnSnmpInSetVars
ibmappnSnmpInSetVars.description: Total number of VARIBLES included in all SET requests to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpOutNoSuchNames.name: ibmappnSnmpOutNoSuchNames
ibmappnSnmpOutNoSuchNames.description: Total number of VARIABLES that could not be found by the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpOutGenErrs.name: ibmappnSnmpOutGenErrs
ibmappnSnmpOutGenErrs.description: Total number of undefined errors that occurred processing SNMP request to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnMemorySize.name: ibmappnMemorySize
ibmappnMemorySize.description: Size of the shared storage segment, as obtained by storage management from the underlying operating system.

ibmappnMemoryUsed.name: ibmappnMemoryUsed
ibmappnMemoryUsed.description: Number of bytes in the segment that are currently allocated to process.

ibmappnMemoryWarnThresh.name: ibmappnMemoryWarnThresh
ibmappnMemoryWarnThresh.description: Allocation threshold beyond which storage management considers the storage resources to be constrained.

ibmappnMemoryCritThresh.name: ibmappnMemoryCritThresh
ibmappnMemoryCritThresh.description: Allocation threshold beyond which storage management considers the storage resources to be critically constrained.

ibmappnNodeDefLsGoodXids.name: ibmappnNodeDefLsGoodXids
ibmappnNodeDefLsGoodXids.description: The current number of successfull XIDs that have occurred on all defined link stations since the last time this node was initialized.

ibmappnNodeDefLsBadXids.name: ibmappnNodeDefLsBadXids
ibmappnNodeDefLsBadXids.description: The current number of unsuccessfull XIDs that have occurred on all defined link stations since the last time this node was initialized.

ibmappnNodeDynLsGoodXids.name: ibmappnNodeDynLsGoodXids
ibmappnNodeDynLsGoodXids.description: The current number of successfull XIDs that have occurred on all dynamic link stations since the last time this node was initialized.

ibmappnNodeDynLsBadXids.name: ibmappnNodeDynLsBadXids
ibmappnNodeDynLsBadXids.description: The current number of unsuccessfull XIDs that have occurred on all dynamic link stations since the last time this node was initialized.

ibmappnNnTopoMaxNodes.name: ibmappnNnTopoMaxNodes
ibmappnNnTopoMaxNodes.description: Maximum number of nodes allowed in the APPN topology database. This administratively assigned value must be equal to or greater than the maximum total number of end nodes and network nodes. If the number of nodes exceeds this value, APPN will issue an Alert and the node can no longer participate as a network node.

ibmappnNnTopoCurNumNodes.name: ibmappnNnTopoCurNumNodes
ibmappnNnTopoCurNumNodes.description: Current number of nodes in this node's topology database. If this value exceeds the maximum number of nodes allowed (NnTopoMaxNodes), APPN alert CPDB002 is issued.

ibmappnNnTopoInTdus.name: ibmappnNnTopoInTdus
ibmappnNnTopoInTdus.description: Total number of TDUs received from all adjacent NN since last initialization.

ibmappnNnTopoOutTdus.name: ibmappnNnTopoOutTdus
ibmappnNnTopoOutTdus.description: Total number of TDUs built by this node to be sent to all adjacent NN since last initialization.

ibmappnNnTopoNodeLowRsns.name: ibmappnNnTopoNodeLowRsns
ibmappnNnTopoNodeLowRsns.description: Total number of topology node updates received by this node with a RSN less than the current RSN. Both even and odd RSN are included in this count. These TDUs are not errors, but result when TDUs are broadcast to all adjacent network nodes. No update to this node's topology database occurs, but this node will send a TDU with it's higher RSN to the adjacent node that sent this low RSN.

ibmappnNnTopoNodeEqualRsns.name: ibmappnNnTopoNodeEqualRsns
ibmappnNnTopoNodeEqualRsns.description: Total number of topology node updates received by this node with a RSN equal to the current RSN. Both even and odd RSN are included in this count. These TDUs are not errors, but result when TDUs are broadcast to all adjacent network nodes. No update to this node's topology database occurs.

ibmappnNnTopoNodeGoodHighRsns.name: ibmappnNnTopoNodeGoodHighRsns
ibmappnNnTopoNodeGoodHighRsns.description: Total number of topology node updates received by this node with a RSN greater than the current RSN. This results in updating this nodes topology and broadcasting a TDU to all adjacent network nodes. It is not required to send a TDU to the sender of this update because that node already has the update.

ibmappnNnTopoNodeBadHighRsns.name: ibmappnNnTopoNodeBadHighRsns
ibmappnNnTopoNodeBadHighRsns.description: Total number of topology node updates received by this node with an odd RSN greater than the current RSN. These updates represent a topology inconsistency detected by one of the APPN network nodes. This results in updating this nodes topology and broadcasting a TDU to all adjacent network nodes.

ibmappnNnTopoNodeStateUpdates.name: ibmappnNnTopoNodeStateUpdates
ibmappnNnTopoNodeStateUpdates.description: Total number of topology Node records built as a result of internally detected node state changes that affect APPN topology and routing. Updates are sent via TDUs to all adjacent network nodes.

ibmappnNnTopoNodeErrors.name: ibmappnNnTopoNodeErrors
ibmappnNnTopoNodeErrors.description: Total number of topology node records inconsistencies detected by this node. This occurs when this node attempts to update its topology database and detects a data inconsistency. This node will create a TDU with the current RSN incremented to the next odd number and broadcast it to all adjacent NNs.

ibmappnNnTopoNodeTimerUpdates.name: ibmappnNnTopoNodeTimerUpdates
ibmappnNnTopoNodeTimerUpdates.description: Total number of topology node records built for this node's resource due to timer updates. Updates are sent via TDUs to all adjacent network nodes. These updates insure other network nodes do not delete this node's resources from their topology database.

ibmappnNnTopoNodePurges.name: ibmappnNnTopoNodePurges
ibmappnNnTopoNodePurges.description: Total number of topology node records purged from this node's topology database. This occurs when a node has not been updated in a specified amount of time. The owning node is responsible for broadcasting updates for its resource that it wants kept in the network topology.

ibmappnNnTopoTgLowRsns.name: ibmappnNnTopoTgLowRsns
ibmappnNnTopoTgLowRsns.description: Total number of topology TG updates received by this node with a RSN less than the current RSN. Both even and odd RSN are included in this count. These TDUs are not errors, but result when TDUs are broadcast to all adjacent network nodes. No update to this node's topology database occurs, but this node will send a TDU with it's higher RSN to the sender of the low RSN.

ibmappnNnTopoTgEqualRsns.name: ibmappnNnTopoTgEqualRsns
ibmappnNnTopoTgEqualRsns.description: Total number of topology TG updates received by this node with a RSN equal to the current RSN. Both even and odd RSN are included in this count. These TDUs are not errors, but result when TDUs are broadcast to all adjacent network nodes. No update to this node's topology database occurs.

ibmappnNnTopoTgGoodHighRsns.name: ibmappnNnTopoTgGoodHighRsns
ibmappnNnTopoTgGoodHighRsns.description: Total number of topology TG updates received by this node with a RSN greater than the current RSN. This results in updating this nodes topology and broadcasting the update to all adjacent network nodes.

ibmappnNnTopoTgBadHighRsns.name: ibmappnNnTopoTgBadHighRsns
ibmappnNnTopoTgBadHighRsns.description: Total number of topology TG updates received by this node with an odd RSN greater than the current RSN. These updates represent a topology inconsistency detected by one of the APPN network nodes. This results in updating this nodes topology and broadcasting a TDU to all adjacent network nodes.

ibmappnNnTopoTgStateUpdates.name: ibmappnNnTopoTgStateUpdates
ibmappnNnTopoTgStateUpdates.description: Total number of topology TG records built as a result of internally detected node state changes that affect APPN topology and routing. Updates are sent via TDUs to all adjacent network nodes.

ibmappnNnTopoTgErrors.name: ibmappnNnTopoTgErrors
ibmappnNnTopoTgErrors.description: Total number of topology TG records inconsistencies detected by this node. This occurs when this node attempts to update its topology database and detects a data inconsistency. This node will create a TDU with the current RSN incremented to the next odd number and broadcast it to all adjacent NNs.

ibmappnNnTopoTgTimerUpdates.name: ibmappnNnTopoTgTimerUpdates
ibmappnNnTopoTgTimerUpdates.description: Total number of topology TG records built for this node's resource due to timer updates. Updates are sent via TDUs to all adjacent network nodes. These updates insure other network nodes do not delete this node's resources from their topology database.

ibmappnNnTopoTgPurges.name: ibmappnNnTopoTgPurges
ibmappnNnTopoTgPurges.description: Total number of topology TG records purged from this node's topology database. This occurs when a TG has not been updated in a specified amount of time. The owning node is responsible for broadcasting updates for its resource that it wants to keep in the network topology.

ibmappnNnTopoTotalRouteCalcs.name: ibmappnNnTopoTotalRouteCalcs
ibmappnNnTopoTotalRouteCalcs.description: Number of routes calculated for all class of services since the last initialization.

ibmappnNnTopoTotalRouteRejs.name: ibmappnNnTopoTotalRouteRejs
ibmappnNnTopoTotalRouteRejs.description: Number of route requests for all class of services that could not be calculated since last initialization.

ibmappnNnTopoRouteTable.name: ibmappnNnTopoRouteTable
ibmappnNnTopoRouteTable.description: Table containing an entry for every Class of Service that it has calculated a route for.

ibmappnNnTopoRouteEntry.name: ibmappnNnTopoRouteEntry
ibmappnNnTopoRouteEntry.description: The Class of Service name is the index for this table.

ibmappnNnTopoRouteCos.name: ibmappnNnTopoRouteCos
ibmappnNnTopoRouteCos.description: The Class of Service for the route.

ibmappnNnTopoRouteTrees.name: ibmappnNnTopoRouteTrees
ibmappnNnTopoRouteTrees.description: Number of routes tree caches built for this Class of Service since the last initialization.

ibmappnNnTopoRouteCalcs.name: ibmappnNnTopoRouteCalcs
ibmappnNnTopoRouteCalcs.description: Number of routes calculated since last initialization.

ibmappnNnTopoRouteRejs.name: ibmappnNnTopoRouteRejs
ibmappnNnTopoRouteRejs.description: Number of route requests that could not be calculated since last initialization.

ibmappnNnAdjNodeTable.name: ibmappnNnAdjNodeTable
ibmappnNnAdjNodeTable.description: Table containing an entry for every node. The information kept in this table is the last FRSN sent and received, the status of the CP-CP sessions, and a gauge that indicates the number of outstanding TDUs.

ibmappnNnAdjNodeEntry.name: ibmappnNnAdjNodeEntry
ibmappnNnAdjNodeEntry.description: The adjacent node name is the index for this table.

ibmappnNnAdjNodeAdjName.name: ibmappnNnAdjNodeAdjName
ibmappnNnAdjNodeAdjName.description: An administratively-assigned fully-qualified name of this node's adjacent network node.

ibmappnNnAdjNodeCpCpSessStatus.name: ibmappnNnAdjNodeCpCpSessStatus
ibmappnNnAdjNodeCpCpSessStatus.description: Indicates the state of CP-CP sessions between this node and adjacent network and end nodes. Incative indicates no CP-CP sessions exists between this node and the adjacent node. Active indicates CP-CP sessons are active using both the ConWinner and ConLoser sessions. The session initiated by this node is refered to as the ConWinner session and is used by this node to send to the adjacent node. The ConLoserr session is initiated by the adjacent node and is used by this node to receive from the adjacent node.

ibmappnNnAdjNodeOutOfSeqTdus.name: ibmappnNnAdjNodeOutOfSeqTdus
ibmappnNnAdjNodeOutOfSeqTdus.description: Number of out of sequence Topology Database Updates (TDUs). In a quiesced state, this value is zero. In normal operation, the value varies depending on the network environment.

ibmappnNnAdjNodeLastFrsnSent.name: ibmappnNnAdjNodeLastFrsnSent
ibmappnNnAdjNodeLastFrsnSent.description: Flow reduction sequence numbers (FRSNs) are associated with Topology Database Updates (TDUs) and are unique only within each APPN network node. A TDU can be associated with multiple APPN resources. This FRSN indicates the last TDU sent to this adjacent node.

ibmappnNnAdjNodeLastFrsnRcvd.name: ibmappnNnAdjNodeLastFrsnRcvd
ibmappnNnAdjNodeLastFrsnRcvd.description: Flow reduction sequence numbers (FRSNs) are associated with Topology Database Updates (TDUs) and are unique only within each APPN network node. A TDU can be associated with multiple APPN resources. This FRSN indicates the last TDU received from this adjacent node.

ibmappnNnTopologyTable.name: ibmappnNnTopologyTable
ibmappnNnTopologyTable.description: Portion of the APPN routing table that describes all of the APPN network nodes and virtual nodes known to this node.

ibmappnNnTopologyEntry.name: ibmappnNnTopologyEntry
ibmappnNnTopologyEntry.description: The fully-qualified node name is used to index this table.

ibmappnNnNodeName.name: ibmappnNnNodeName
ibmappnNnNodeName.description: Administratively-assigned network name that is locally defined at each network node in the format NETID.CPNAME.

ibmappnNnNodeFrsn.name: ibmappnNnNodeFrsn
ibmappnNnNodeFrsn.description: Flow reduction sequence numbers (FRSNs) are associated with Topology Database Updates (TDUs) and are unique only within each APPN network node. A TDU can be associated with multiple APPN resources. This FRSN indicates the last time this resource was updated at this node.

ibmappnNnNodeEntryTimeLeft.name: ibmappnNnNodeEntryTimeLeft
ibmappnNnNodeEntryTimeLeft.description: Number of days before deletion of this network node entry. Range is 0-31.

ibmappnNnNodeRsn.name: ibmappnNnNodeRsn
ibmappnNnNodeRsn.description: Resource sequence number that is assigned and controlled by the network node that owns this resource. This is always an even 32-bit number unless an error has occurred.

ibmappnNnNodeRouteAddResist.name: ibmappnNnNodeRouteAddResist
ibmappnNnNodeRouteAddResist.description: Route addition resistance indicates the relative desirability of using this node for intermediate session traffic. The value, which can be any integer 0-255, is used in route computation. The lower the value, the more desirable the node is for intermediate routing.

ibmappnNnNodeCongested.name: ibmappnNnNodeCongested
ibmappnNnNodeCongested.description: Indicates whether this node is congested. This node is not be included in route selection by other nodes when this congestion exists.

ibmappnNnNodeIsrDepleted.name: ibmappnNnNodeIsrDepleted
ibmappnNnNodeIsrDepleted.description: Indicates whether intermediate session routing resources are depleted. This node is not included in intermediate route selection by other nodes when resources are depleted.

ibmappnNnNodeEndptDepleted.name: ibmappnNnNodeEndptDepleted
ibmappnNnNodeEndptDepleted.description: Indicates whether session endpoint resources are depleted.

ibmappnNnNodeQuiescing.name: ibmappnNnNodeQuiescing
ibmappnNnNodeQuiescing.description: Indicates whether the node is quiescing. This node is not included in route selection by other nodes when the node is quiescing.

ibmappnNnNodeGateway.name: ibmappnNnNodeGateway
ibmappnNnNodeGateway.description: Indicates whether the node provide gateway functions.

ibmappnNnNodeCentralDirectory.name: ibmappnNnNodeCentralDirectory
ibmappnNnNodeCentralDirectory.description: Indicates whether the node is central directory.

ibmappnNnNodeIsr.name: ibmappnNnNodeIsr
ibmappnNnNodeIsr.description: Indicates whether the node supports intermediate session routing (ISR).

ibmappnNnNodeChainSupport.name: ibmappnNnNodeChainSupport
ibmappnNnNodeChainSupport.description: Indicates whether the node supports chaining.

ibmappnNnTgTopologyTable.name: ibmappnNnTgTopologyTable
ibmappnNnTgTopologyTable.description: Portion of the APPN topology database that describes all of the APPN transmissions groups used by the APPN network nodes.

ibmappnNnTgTopologyEntry.name: ibmappnNnTgTopologyEntry
ibmappnNnTgTopologyEntry.description: This table requires three indexes to provide a unique index. The indexes are the owning or originating CPname, the destination CPname, and the TG number.

ibmappnNnTgOwner.name: ibmappnNnTgOwner
ibmappnNnTgOwner.description: Administratively-assigned name for the originating node for this TG. The format is NETID.CPNAME and is the same name specified in the node table.

ibmappnNnTgDest.name: ibmappnNnTgDest
ibmappnNnTgDest.description: Administratively-assigned fully-qualified network name for the destination node for this TG.

ibmappnNnTgNum.name: ibmappnNnTgNum
ibmappnNnTgNum.description: Number associated with this transmission group. Range is 0-255.

ibmappnNnTgFrsn.name: ibmappnNnTgFrsn
ibmappnNnTgFrsn.description: Flow reduction sequence numbers (FRSNs) are associated with Topology Database Updates (TDUs) and are unique only within each APPN network node. A TDU can be associated with multiple APPN resources. This FRSN indicates the last time this resource was updated at this node.

ibmappnNnTgEntryTimeLeft.name: ibmappnNnTgEntryTimeLeft
ibmappnNnTgEntryTimeLeft.description: Number of days before deletion of this network node TG entry. Range is 0-31.

ibmappnNnTgDestVirtual.name: ibmappnNnTgDestVirtual
ibmappnNnTgDestVirtual.description: Indicates whether the destination node is a virtual node.

ibmappnNnTgDlcData.name: ibmappnNnTgDlcData
ibmappnNnTgDlcData.description: DLC specific data related to the link connection network. Token-Ring - MAC/SAP X.25 Switched - dial digits X.21 Switched - dial digits Circuit Swtch - dial digits

ibmappnNnTgRsn.name: ibmappnNnTgRsn
ibmappnNnTgRsn.description: Current owning node's resource sequence number for this resource.

ibmappnNnTgOperational.name: ibmappnNnTgOperational
ibmappnNnTgOperational.description: Indicates whether the transmission group is operational.

ibmappnNnTgQuiescing.name: ibmappnNnTgQuiescing
ibmappnNnTgQuiescing.description: Indicates whether the transmission group is quiescing.

ibmappnNnTgCpCpSession.name: ibmappnNnTgCpCpSession
ibmappnNnTgCpCpSession.description: Indicates whether CP-CP sessions are supported on this TG.

ibmappnNnTgEffCap.name: ibmappnNnTgEffCap
ibmappnNnTgEffCap.description: The effective capacity is an integer value that indicates the kilo bits per second. It is derived from the link bandwidth and maximum load factor with the range of 0 thru 603,979,776. This is an administratively assigned value associated with this TG.

ibmappnNnTgConnCost.name: ibmappnNnTgConnCost
ibmappnNnTgConnCost.description: Cost per connect time: a value representing the relative cost per unit of time to use the TG. Range is from 0, which means no cost, to 255, which indicates maximum cost. This is an administratively assigned value associated with this TG.

ibmappnNnTgByteCost.name: ibmappnNnTgByteCost
ibmappnNnTgByteCost.description: Relative cost of transmitting a byte over this link. Range is from 0 (lowest cost) to 255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with this TG.

ibmappnNnTgSecurity.name: ibmappnNnTgSecurity
ibmappnNnTgSecurity.description: The security is represented as an integer with a range of 1 thru 255 with the most common values enumerated as defined above. This is an administratively assigned value associated with this TG.

ibmappnNnTgDelay.name: ibmappnNnTgDelay
ibmappnNnTgDelay.description: Relative amount of time that it takes for a signal to travel the length of the logical link. This time is represented in micro seconds, with some of the more common values enumerated. This is an administratively assigned value associated with this TG.

ibmappnNnTgModemClass.name: ibmappnNnTgModemClass
ibmappnNnTgModemClass.description: This is used to have multiple images for a connection network. For a connection network it is the same as in the TG vector; for a non-connection network it is X'00'.

ibmappnNnTgUsr1.name: ibmappnNnTgUsr1
ibmappnNnTgUsr1.description: First user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with this TG.

ibmappnNnTgUsr2.name: ibmappnNnTgUsr2
ibmappnNnTgUsr2.description: Second user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with this TG.

ibmappnNnTgUsr3.name: ibmappnNnTgUsr3
ibmappnNnTgUsr3.description: Third user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with this TG.

ibmappnNnTopologyFRTable.name: ibmappnNnTopologyFRTable
ibmappnNnTopologyFRTable.description: Portion of the APPN routing table that describes all of the APPN network nodes and virtual nodes known to this node.

ibmappnNnNodeFRName.name: ibmappnNnNodeFRName
ibmappnNnNodeFRName.description: Administratively-assigned network name that is locally defined at each network node in the format NETID.CPNAME.

ibmappnNnNodeFRQuiescing.description: Indicates whether the node is quiescing. This node is not included in route selection by other nodes when the node is quiescing.

ibmappnNnNodeFRGateway.description: Indicates whether the node provide gateway functions.

ibmappnNnNodeFRCentralDirectory.description: Indicates whether the node is central directory.

ibmappnNnNodeFRIsr.description: Indicates whether the node supports intermediate session routing (ISR).

ibmappnNnNodeFRChainSupport.name: ibmappnNnNodeFRChainSupport
ibmappnNnNodeFRChainSupport.description: Indicates whether the node supports chaining.

ibmappnNnTgTopologyFRTable.description: Portion of the APPN topology database that describes all of the APPN transmissions groups used by the APPN network nodes.

ibmappnNnTgTopologyFREntry.description: This table is indexed by four columns: FRSN, TG owner fully-qualified node name, TG destination fully-qualified node name, and TG number.

ibmappnNnTgFRNum.name: ibmappnNnTgFRNum
ibmappnNnTgFRNum.description: Number associated with this transmission group. Range is 0-255.
